title: For Sale/Trade:  NICEST CETME AROUND LOOK! .308
postcontent:
WILL SEND MORE PICS JUST EMAIL ME!
CETME is the predescessor to the HK rifles. Its cambered in 7.62x51/.308 NATO. Semi-Automatic, closed bolt, gas operated. Very nice furniture, stamped steel reciever, forged steel guts. I have reason to belive this particular rifle was issued to most likely Spanish or Argtine troops, possibly circa the Falkland Islands Conflict. The only bad part about CETME rifles is tat CAI never put a date stamp on them, so there is no real way to know how old it is. It does have a very low serial nuber. In the way of CETME's this is a beauty and a rarity. They are renowned for their ability to be shot, blown-up, run-over, submerged, and generally beat up,but still perform without malfuntion and do so with remarkable accuracy. Many CETME rifles have issues with "bolt head space" This is the gap found between the bolt and bolt carrier group when the bolt is in the foreward position. My CETME has virtually NO HEADSPACE GAP. Some are also known to have charging handle malfuncions, mine doesnt. This particular rifle is in outstanding condition. The furniture shows wear less than most, reciever and barrel are like new. All interal parts are also like new. Most parts on this are interchangable with HK G3 parts, but not all. Comes with 9 magazines, and fully assembled and fully functioning CAI CETME. The best things about the CETME is its accuracy, durability, and its cartridge. The .308 has more ballistic energy at a half mile than a .357 Magnum at point blank range. This is a serious weapon, and a tack driver to boot. Let me know if your interested, Its really worth your deepest consideration.

title: For Sale:  New Knoxx Spec Ops Folding Stock for Rem 870 12 Gauge
postcontent:
Product Information

The SpecOps folding stock offers compact storage and the ability to reduce perceived recoil by as much as 65%, even with the stock folded. The rubber coated wire-frame stock incorporates a rubber butt pad and is easy to fold over the top of the receiver for storage or transport. Recoil reduction is accomplished via the heavy spring within the pistol grip that is connected to, and provides resistance against, the shotgun receiver as it moves up and to the rear along an inclined surface during recoil. The receiver's movement and spring's resistance absorb a large amount of the recoil produced upon firing, meaning the shooter experiences significantly less unpleasantness.
